Kaveel Singh, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A man was stabbed to death in Pietermaritzburg in the early hours of Saturday morning, paramedic services said. &ldquo;A man believed to be in his 30's was killed after sustaining a single stab wound to his chest on the corner of West and Church streets in Pietermaritzburg,&rdquo; ER24 spokesperson Annine Siddall said.According to Siddall, paramedics arrived at a hostile scene and found the man lying on the road. &ldquo;The man was surrounded by a group of 20 to 30 people at the time. Unfortunately there was nothing ER24 paramedics could do to save the man and he was declared dead on the scene.&rdquo;She added: &ldquo;It is not yet known how the man was killed, but local authorities were on the scene for further investigations.&rdquo;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.